to get what you're thinking♪

14
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:13,140
♪A ballad to our journey♪

15
00:01:14,490 --> 00:01:17,620
♪Pursuing the dream of our youth♪

16
00:01:17,620 --> 00:01:20,570
♪We take everything as it comes♪

17
00:01:20,770 --> 00:01:23,790
♪The distant land might be dangerous♪

18
00:01:23,790 --> 00:01:26,640
♪But what's life without an adventure?♪

19
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:29,710
♪Youths are supposed to dream big and be sharp♪

20
00:01:29,940 --> 00:01:33,020
♪Every struggle in life has taught us♪

21
00:01:33,020 --> 00:01:34,970
♪That we shall do what we can wherever we go♪

22
00:01:34,970 --> 00:01:40,490
♪Together, another journey awaits♪

23
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:50,020
[The Blood of Youth]

24
00:01:50,250 --> 00:01:52,970
[Episode 13]

25
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:03,590
Your Highness, please have some tea.

26
00:02:06,350 --> 00:02:06,790
Have a seat.

27
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:15,030
It's been a long time since I last saw you.

28
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:17,240
I didn't expect

29
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:18,910
to let you see this mess

30
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:20,590
when I met you again.

31
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:22,190
It's okay.

32
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,430
No matter how terrible the situation is,

33
00:02:25,030 --> 00:02:26,590
I can't see it.

34
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:28,710
Sorry, I misspoke.

35
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:31,030
I was just

36
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,520
kidding with you.

37
00:02:34,430 --> 00:02:36,120
The jokes you make

38
00:02:36,430 --> 00:02:38,280
are never funny.

39
00:02:40,870 --> 00:02:41,710
I remember

40
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:43,750
whenever I saw you as a kid,

41
00:02:44,630 --> 00:02:45,630
you would always tell me

42
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,000
not to be too hard on myself.

43
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:49,470
You advised me to be happy,

44
00:02:50,190 --> 00:02:50,840
to smile more.

45
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:52,680
I remember it

46
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,710
all these years,

47
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,960
but when I see you again,

48
00:02:57,870 --> 00:02:58,960
you still think

49
00:02:59,030 --> 00:03:00,030
I'm not humorous.

50
00:03:01,590 --> 00:03:02,190
That's not true.

51
00:03:03,030 --> 00:03:04,280
You're more humorous

52
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:06,800
than before.

53
00:03:09,030 --> 00:03:09,470
Fine.

54
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,910
Compared to the other princes,

55
00:03:12,710 --> 00:03:13,840
because of my eyes,

56
00:03:14,590 --> 00:03:15,960
I am indeed somewhat more pathetic.

57
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,030
Thank you

58
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,870
for your help today.

59
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:22,680
Even if I didn't take action,

60
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,000
you'd be able to take care of it

61
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,520
easily,

62
00:03:27,630 --> 00:03:28,240
but just

63
00:03:28,630 --> 00:03:29,560
a little slower.

64
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,310
I have an urgent matter today,

65
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:35,280
so I overstepped my authority.

66
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:37,750
But I wonder

67
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,800
what urgent matter

68
00:03:39,310 --> 00:03:40,120
you are talking about.

69
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,750
I have a decree to pass on.

70
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,030
Don't worry.

71
00:03:46,630 --> 00:03:47,360
This decree

72
00:03:48,590 --> 00:03:49,630
is not meant for the Vermilion Bird.

73
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,430
I haven't been the Vermilion Bird

74
00:03:57,680 --> 00:03:58,870
for years.

75
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,030
I'm just

76
00:04:00,710 --> 00:04:01,240
a steward

77
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:03,430
of Xueyue City.

78
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,080
Then, I'll call you

79
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,240
City Lord Sikong.

80
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:10,150
It sounds much better

81
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,240
this way.

82
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:14,870
This decree

83
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,310
is meant for that person.

84
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,750
In fact, before today,

85
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,160
I wasn't sure

86
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:22,870
if he was really here

87
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:24,680
until just now.

88
00:04:25,630 --> 00:04:26,560
Although I couldn't see it,

89
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:28,750
his habit

90
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:30,510
of surprising

91
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,560
and scaring people

92
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:34,830
has not changed over the years.

93
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:37,510
This matter

94
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,870
is between you two.

95
00:04:40,270 --> 00:04:42,480
This has nothing to do with Xueyue City.

96
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:45,950
I heard

97
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:48,720
he apprenticed to you.

98
00:04:49,190 --> 00:04:50,680
I wanted to take him as my disciple.

99
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,070
He neither agreed

100
00:04:52,510 --> 00:04:53,510
nor refused.

101
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:55,830
I get it now.

102
00:04:57,390 --> 00:04:58,560
City Lord Sikong

103
00:04:59,070 --> 00:05:00,430
is trying to make sure Xueyue City

104
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:01,950
stays out of

105
00:05:02,630 --> 00:05:03,630
this matter.

106
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,160
There are very few people

107
00:05:06,870 --> 00:05:08,480
in this world who dare refuse to accept

108
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:09,870
His Majesty's decrees,

109
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,950
and even fewer who accept them

110
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:13,510
and then disobey them.

111
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:16,630
But he happens to be one of them.

112
00:05:18,190 --> 00:05:19,040
So what's wrong with me

113
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:20,950
wanting nothing to do

114
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:22,680
with this matter?

115
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:30,870
I see.

116
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:36,310
It's all your fault.

117
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:38,240
Why didn't you

118
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,430
fight longer?

119
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:40,750
You were in such a hurry to get down there

120
00:05:41,270 --> 00:05:42,430
because you were afraid
that Qianluo would surrender

121
00:05:42,870 --> 00:05:43,720
and you'd have to marry her, right?

122
00:05:44,190 --> 00:05:44,720
Lei Wujie,

123
00:05:45,630 --> 00:05:46,240
if you keep talking nonsense,

124
00:05:46,390 --> 00:05:47,390
I'll rip your mouth off.

125
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:49,560
Who would want to surrender first?

126
00:05:50,510 --> 00:05:51,800
Who would want to marry this guy?

127
00:05:52,830 --> 00:05:53,190
Qianluo,

128
00:05:54,310 --> 00:05:54,830
this time,

129
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:55,830
Xiao Se was of great help.

130
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,240
If it weren't for him,

131
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:58,870
things would have become
much more complicated today.

132
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,830
And for Luo Mingxuan,

133
00:06:01,310 --> 00:06:02,190
you should go and visit him

134
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:03,190
when he's recovered.

135
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,120
He could have beaten Duan Xuanheng

136
00:06:05,390 --> 00:06:06,190
for you

137
00:06:06,190 --> 00:06:06,800
if he wasn't poisoned.

138
00:06:09,830 --> 00:06:10,190
Xiao Se,

139
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,070
thanks.

140
00:06:12,310 --> 00:06:12,720
You're welcome.

141
00:06:13,390 --> 00:06:14,040
I will pay

142
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,430
what I owe.

143
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:16,560
If you

144
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:17,630
ever need me to fight for you,

145
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,390
I will not hesitate

146
00:06:19,830 --> 00:06:20,950
to return the favor.

147
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:22,430
It's fine.

148
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:26,560
Aren't you

149
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,720
usually quite helpful?

150
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:29,680
Why are you

151
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:30,480
pulling a long face all day?

152
00:06:31,950 --> 00:06:32,920
Who's helpful?

153
00:06:33,190 --> 00:06:33,830
You.

154
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:35,680
Listen,

155
00:06:36,190 --> 00:06:37,510
I didn't even ask him to go up today,

156
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:38,480
and he

157
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:39,720
rushed up.

158
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:41,040
Really?

159
00:06:41,630 --> 00:06:42,240
Of course.

160
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,630
I did it

161
00:06:44,870 --> 00:06:45,750
because that Duan fellow

162
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:46,750
was so annoying

163
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:48,830
and I just couldn't stand him.

164
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,190
That's fine.

165
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,040
Anyway,

166
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:52,830
I approve

167
00:06:53,510 --> 00:06:53,950
of you today.

168
00:06:54,950 --> 00:06:56,000
Do I need your approval?

169
00:06:57,390 --> 00:06:57,600
But...

170
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:00,120
Enough.

171
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:01,270
Leave it at that.

172
00:07:02,190 --> 00:07:03,160
The tournament

173
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,160
is finally over.

174
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,600
Lord Bai can also prove

175
00:07:06,830 --> 00:07:07,870
the fairness of the tournament on the spot.

176
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:09,310
I don't think

177
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:10,630
they would dare
to say anything else in the future.

178
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:11,720
Yes, Lian.

179
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:13,830
That prince is so dashing.

180
00:07:14,510 --> 00:07:15,480
Hundreds of people at the scene

181
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:16,920
fell to their knees at once.

182
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:18,430
But

183
00:07:19,070 --> 00:07:20,750
why did the City Lord only do the half-kneeling?

184
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:23,000
Third Master was once the Vermilion Bird,

185
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,560
one of the Four Guardians of Tianqi City.

186
00:07:24,830 --> 00:07:25,920
He could make a half salute
in front of the Emperor,

187
00:07:26,190 --> 00:07:26,720
so naturally a prince

188
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,040
is not qualified to have him

189
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:28,680
make a full salute.

190
00:07:30,390 --> 00:07:32,180
It turns out that the City Lord
was once the Vermilion Bird.

191
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:33,950
Wouldn't that make Qianluo

192
00:07:34,510 --> 00:07:35,240
the heiress to the Vermilion Bird Token?

193
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,310
Father told me about it.

194
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,040
But I'm not interested.

195
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,000
I don't know that person,

196
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,000
so why should I be a guardian?

197
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:44,870
Right,

198
00:07:45,830 --> 00:07:47,120
my father can do the half-kneeling,

199
00:07:47,630 --> 00:07:48,830
but why didn't you kneel, Xiao Se?

200
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:50,720
Yeah.

201
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,360
I...

202
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:57,600
have weak legs.

203
00:07:59,560 --> 00:07:59,920
What...

204
00:08:00,070 --> 00:08:00,430
Lian,

205
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,600
look, he's making things up again.

206
00:08:04,190 --> 00:08:05,390
I have some ancestral glory

207
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:07,270
that allows me to not kneel before the Emperor.

208
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:08,720
Do you think this answer is okay?

209
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:10,120
Really?

210
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,680
You're so stingy,

211
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,430
but you actually come
from a distinguished family?

212
00:08:19,310 --> 00:08:20,040
Right, Lian,

213
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,070
why did

214
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:22,950
a prince from Tianqi City

215
00:08:23,430 --> 00:08:24,560
come to Xueyue City?

216
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:26,240
He should have

217
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:26,870
something important

218
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,160
to discuss with Third Master.

219
00:08:28,870 --> 00:08:29,560
After all, Third Master

220
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,120
was once the Vermilion Bird.

221
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,000
Third Master was credited

222
00:08:33,630 --> 00:08:34,840
with the ascension of His Majesty to the throne.

223
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:36,600
But the sudden arrival
of the Prince of Tianqi City

224
00:08:36,790 --> 00:08:37,790
in Xueyue City

225
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:39,720
gives me a feeling of unease.

226
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,240
My father has long said

227
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:42,600
that he hates the people

228
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:43,600
in that city.

229
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:45,480
But I think

230
00:08:45,550 --> 00:08:47,390
Lord Bai is a good man.

231
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:49,000
However,

232
00:08:49,870 --> 00:08:51,630
there is something wrong with his eyes.

233
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:56,440
Because he can't see anything.

234
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:58,390
Can't see anything?

235
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:01,390
He took a piece of cake

236
00:09:01,390 --> 00:09:02,150
from someone's plate

237
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:03,030
when he was little,

238
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:05,320
and he went blind after eating it.

239
00:09:07,030 --> 00:09:08,080
All these years, Emperor Mingde

240
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:09,150
had searched all over the world
for competent physicians,

241
00:09:09,150 --> 00:09:10,390
but he just couldn't be cured.

242
00:09:12,630 --> 00:09:13,910
What a poor man.

243
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:16,720
Xiao Se.

244
00:09:19,470 --> 00:09:20,000
Elder Yin.

245
00:09:23,270 --> 00:09:24,390
Lord Bai is waiting for you in the backyard.

246
00:09:24,670 --> 00:09:25,270
You go there first.

247
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:35,440
Elder Yin.

248
00:09:36,150 --> 00:09:36,480
Well,

249
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:38,200
what does Lord Bai want with Xiao Se?

250
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,510
They should have studied together

251
00:09:40,670 --> 00:09:41,200
at Tianqi Academy.

252
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:46,000
So they were classmates.

253
00:09:48,270 --> 00:09:49,000
Classmates.

254
00:09:52,340 --> 00:09:56,620
[Stay Simple, Stay True]

255
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:13,600
I am blind.

256
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,320
I can't see you,

257
00:10:16,790 --> 00:10:17,960
but you can see me.

258
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:19,840
What's wrong?

259
00:10:20,790 --> 00:10:21,870
Since you've seen me,

260
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:23,750
aren't you going to greet me?

261
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,440
Greetings, Your Highness, Lord Bai.

262
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,080
Is that the way you address me?

263
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,120
I am just a commoner.

264
00:10:38,630 --> 00:10:39,200
What else can I address you

265
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,670
when I meet the Second Prince,

266
00:10:41,150 --> 00:10:42,080
Lord Bai?

267
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:45,030
After all, addressing you incorrectly
will get me killed.

268
00:10:46,790 --> 00:10:47,750
Do you know

269
00:10:49,030 --> 00:10:50,200
that not kneeling before me
in the morning just now

270
00:10:51,390 --> 00:10:52,390
is punishable by death?

271
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,240
My head is right here.

272
00:10:56,550 --> 00:10:58,510
Take it if you like.

273
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:06,480
You don't speak as harshly

274
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,150
as you used to.

275
00:11:08,550 --> 00:11:10,720
You sound a little bit weak.

276
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:12,840
But you're still

277
00:11:13,870 --> 00:11:15,000
as cheeky as ever.

278
00:11:20,390 --> 00:11:21,870
You might as well call me Chong.

279
00:11:24,910 --> 00:11:26,240
I haven't heard that for years.

280
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:28,910
I'm Xiao Se.

281
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:31,320
I am just

282
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,430
the owner of an ordinary inn.

283
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:33,910
I have no right

284
00:11:33,910 --> 00:11:35,750
to address Lord Bai as Chong.

285
00:11:36,750 --> 00:11:37,270
All right.

286
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,480
Xiao Se of Snowfall Villa.

287
00:11:40,910 --> 00:11:41,480
Yes, Your Highness.

288
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:42,670
Accept the decree.

289
00:11:44,550 --> 00:11:45,390
Accept the decree?

290
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:46,480
Accept the decree.

291
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:00,000
By order of His Majesty,

